## 4.2 Character Prompt
Write a standalone casting brief (75–100 words) for Seedream image generation. Front-facing portrait format.
Cover: gender, approximate age, ethnicity, skin tone, hair style and colour, build. One sentence on clothing (key garment, colour, fit). One sentence on overall vibe/energy. Extract these details from the original storyboard's character descriptions. Do NOT invent appearance.

## 4.3 Scene Prompt
Write a standalone environment brief (75–100 words) for Seedream/Seedance. Cover: interior or exterior, specific location type (e.g. "outdoor basketball court", "modern kitchen", "urban street"), dominant surfaces and materials, key props (max 3), primary light source, time of day, colour mood. Base this on the actual scenes described in the original storyboard. Do NOT invent a generic studio setting if the original shows a real location.

## 4.4 Style and Camera Prompt
Write a standalone style and camera brief (50–75 words). Cover: overall visual style (UGC, cinematic, studio, etc.), primary shot types used (close-up, medium, wide), camera movement (handheld, static, slow-zoom), colour grade/mood, and any distinctive visual techniques from the original.

## 4.5 Regeneration Reference
One paragraph (50–75 words) summarising the key visual and narrative elements that must be preserved in any AI-generated version: character identity, location, core message, and CTA.

